# Poker Assist — Caribbean Stud

## AI + Hand logging setup

### 1. Gemini AI (free)
1. Get a key at [Google AI Studio](https://aistudio.google.com/apikey)
2. Open ⚙️ Settings → paste key → **Test Gemini** → Save
3. Set AI coach to **Google Gemini**

AI fires automatically when you log all 5 player cards + dealer up-card.

### 2. Supabase cloud sync (free tier — same as your other apps)
1. Open your Supabase project dashboard
2. SQL Editor → run `supabase/migrations/001_poker_caribbean_hands.sql`
3. Settings → copy **Project URL** and **anon public** key
4. Paste in ⚙️ Settings → Save

Hands sync to `poker_caribbean_hands` table. Without Supabase, hands save locally in your browser.

### 3. Environment variables (optional)
Create `.env.local`:
```
VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY=AIza...
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://xxx.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJ...
```

## What gets logged per hand
- Dealer up-card + full dealer hand
- Your 5 cards + hand rank
- Ante, raise multiplier, raise amount, progressive bet
- Your action (raise/fold)
- AI recommendation + whether you followed it
- Result, P&L, dealer qualified, win/loss

## Trends panel
Shows win rate, P&L, AI follow rate, raise/fold counts, and recent hand history.

## Run
```bash
npm install
npm run dev
```
